Write the complete operational narrative for {domain_name}.

This is a DEDICATED NARRATIVE CALL. Your entire output is the chapter narrative — use the full budget to write the most comprehensive, operationally useful guide you can produce for this exact domain and life event.

MINIMUM 3500 WORDS. Target 4000–5000 words.

Write as a practitioner's manual: what to do, when to do it, how to decide between options, what can go wrong and exactly how to recover, what success looks like at each phase, and how this domain connects to the domains before and after it.

The narrative must feel hand-designed for {life_event}, not adapted from a generic framework. Every example, every failure scenario, every decision point must be specific to this situation. A reader should be able to tell within the first sentence what life event this manual is for.

Return ONLY the following JSON object. No prose. No markdown. No code fences.

{{
  "chapter_number": {chapter_number},
  "domain_id": "domain ID from the chapter plan",
  "chapter_title": "Chapter title from the plan",
  "narrative": "Full operational narrative — minimum 3500 words. Continuous analytical prose, 5–8 sentences per paragraph. No headers, no bullet points inside this field. Opens immediately with the operational situation — no preamble about why this domain matters. Includes explicit decision logic for 4–5 critical judgment calls, at least 3 concrete failure scenarios with real numbers and named mechanisms, phase-by-phase execution guidance with named dependencies, specific professional escalation triggers with conditions and consequences, cross-domain dependencies named from the upstream architecture, and clear closure criteria."
}}
